< review>
I had just broken my last pair of glasses and was finally forced to drive the 25 minutes to give these guys a chance.  Both of my pairs of glasses were pricy (one metal frame and one wire rim). Stopped up here when one of my friends had an oil leak on his motorcycle. The water fountain works luckily, but the office itself is closed Saturday and Sunday. Considering there is no cell service on the mountain, there is a land line at the fire station across the street. One of the few places you can make a call from on the crest. Hung out here for about an hour. Beautiful views.</Text>

<rating>5<//rating>< date>
1524951512860</date>
<pictures>None< /pictures><resp>None</resp><userid>103877571750571734403</userid>< Review>
This is the information station here at the Highway 2 National Forest entrance. At this location you can purchase Daily access passes as well as annual passes. they also have lots of information about the National Forest, with trails, tours, and guides to help you navigate your way through the forest. They also have schedules and updates pertaining specific locations within the forest that close in summer and winter times. be sure to always stop by here to get the latest information about the forest. Also, it is your responsibility to protect the forest from a fire, so be safe!<//Review>

<pictures>None</pictures><resp>None< /resp><GmapID>0x80c2e8e6accd87b1:0x108062b9b29aa263<//GmapID></record></dataset><record>
<Rating>5</Rating><Gmap_id>0x80c2e8e6accd87b1:0x108062b9b29aa263</Gmap_id>< resp>
None<//resp>
<pics>None</pics>< Text>
If you have questions regarding sites in the Angeles Forest or just general do's and don'ts, this is the place you want to visit.

The park ranger was super funny. I had two buns on my head and she got excited and called me a bear. But besides her charm, she was super informative explaining how we couldn't go out in the forest and fire our legal firearms unless we had hunting permits. Online if you look at the information it appears to suggest you can go out to the forest and practice open firing as long as you are away from campers. But she explained how they aren't a open carry Forest. City folk don't know these things.

Overall great information.<//Text>

Ride up through Angeles Forest all the time. Had a mechanical failure on my motorcycle while on Angeles Forest Highway. Staff let us call AAA for a tow (there is no cellular service up here) and had a set of hex wrenches that we were able to borrow.

Latrine is available on-site.< /text>

<text>I cannot believe the negative reviews. Most of them seem to be disgruntled people in general. My experience with Alex and his team has been great. He replaced a motor for me in my 2012 Toyota Prius, and the change went smoothly, for a very reasonable cost, considering the work being done. The engine has a 6 month warranty on it, and at the 3 month mark it start knocking in the motor. I took it back, fearing the worst. After all I had a used motor put in the car, and that carries some risk with it naturally. Alex's team looked at it and determined it was the lifters knocking. They saw the car was throwing a code for a bad sensor. They changed that sensor, replaced the oil, and the knocking went away. I still have 3 months left on the engine warranty too. They were fair about the cost for this and I am very happy with their service. Highly recommended.

The only knock I have is both times I have taken my car in I noticed grease on the door handle and center console where your arm would rest while driving the car. I cleaned this off as it isn't that big a deal and not enough to knock off a star, but would be nice to have the grease cleaned off or have the mechanics wear gloves in the car. Also, they are very very busy so there can sometimes be a wait, but that just shows they know their stuff and they are in demand.< /text>< Resp>

<user>113145384107636870899< /user><user_name>Patrick Rankin</user_name><Date>1347730248606< /Date><Rate>2< /Rate>< Review>
I was recommended this place by friends brother-in-law as a shop that does excellent work at a good price. I took my 86 4runner to P&G Auto for an engine swap (22rec). Please make no mistake, Alex and everyone who works there was very polite and awesome. There is a starting point to consider as well in this review and that is that this motor ran even with a cracked block, I started to remove the valve covers and discovered the crack, at that point took it to P&G. Alex quoted me with an extremely fair price of $1400 with a $700 deposit to start work. After 2 weeks or less I got the call that it would be ready. I took the day off work, and got a ride to Rialto. Waited approx 4 hours and then Alex informed me that it wouldn't be ready that day. No problem, a few more days go by and I get the call that it will be done and ready to pick-up Thursday. Take the day off work, get a ride to Rialto, watched in the shop (I was told it was an open shop and customers may watch) as two different mechanics try to assemble the EFI to the head. First one declared it good as the motor started and I pointed out to him that a considerable amount of gas was leaking out of the bottom of the fuel rail assembly. This repeated twice as the O-rings kept getting pinched from incorrect installation. I was then asked to go wait back upfront because the mechanic was nervous with me watching over his shoulder. Totally understandable, I can be the same way at my job. After 2 more hours, they come upfront and tell me that it won't be ready that day either. I get a call the next week and Alex said they got it running and took it for a test drive and the brakes are bad and the wheel cylinders,master cylinder, and calipers need to be replaced. Ok too the first two, I'll wait on the calipers. Then the fuel pump and alternator were bad. Ok replace those after all they are prob over 20 years old no problem. Get the third call that it will be ready. Leave work early, get a ride to Rialto. Fuel pump STAR AUTO PARTS delivered was a dud. No worries guy is on his way with a new one, no charge, and heres a free star auto parts sweater. Ok I love free stuff. 2 hours and the fuel pump is in, test drive and the idle is a little out of wack, no worries, adjusted the idle and took the truck home. So with understanding to it being an old truck, and more things went wrong than were known the $1400 estimate went to $2750. Ouch but I was glad to have the truck back, I love my Yota. Less than a week out the fuel pump fails on the freeway. P&G brought a tow truck and grabbed me off the 210, much appreciated no cost to me.
This was a year ago and this is where its at now. 2 of the four injectors installed turned out to be used (not rebuilt cores, used). Many of the parts installed on the motor were used and rusted, painted over with black paint which has now peeled. The motor was assembled without the throttle position sensor, the new radiator sprung a leak, alternator will be replaced shortly since when I turn on the headlights the idle drops and the motor sputters. Replacing the fuel pump on principle alone (never buy star auto parts pumps), I just went to replace the header and only two stock studs were there (supposed to be all studs), the rest were bolts, 2 of the bolts were stripped and now I have to re-tap the head.
So is the motor running? barely but it is running. Is P&G all to blame? Absolutely not, some of the sensors and what not could have been damaged when I took it in. However, at the end of the day this is what I take inventory on; I lost 2 days of pay (about $300 wages before taxes) not counting the 1/2 day to pick it up when it was finally ready and asking for rides from work in orange county to Rialto. I have a stripped head bolts, used parts, and a motor that still does not run correct. All for a total cost of about $3000 including time lost, not including personal headache and zero confidence in the motors assembly.< /Review>

< review>
I've normally had a great experience at this location. However today, I believe it was the manager who was in (I don't believe she's been in when I've been before) and she was not very accomodating. My kids wanted the same sandwich so I decided to get a Medium and give them each half. They wanted cheddar on one side, Jack on the other. No biggie, I thought. But the manager refused to do it. She said, "I see what you're trying to do. But you'll need to get two minis to have two different cheeses" (since I was being so sneaky trying to buy one big sandwich for my kids to share, instead of two minis?) She tried to explain to me why "it won't work" but I didn't understand. She looked at me with eyes big and eye brows high and said, "Huh? Do you understand?" Well, I didn't. She further explained that the cheeses melt and it wouldn't work. ???? She decided for me that I wouldn't want two different cheese on a sandwich that might melt together. I didn't push back because I couldn't see this going any better. The environment felt "cold" and unkind... she wasn't even friendly about her refusal. I left feeling like she thought I was stupid (which she was happy to expose publicly). Even my 11 and 9 year olds mentioned how rudely I'd been treated after we'd left.

As I said at the start, I've normally had a great experience here. I've only been a handful of times, but we LOVE Deli Delicious. Unfortunately, I may avoid this one because of the poor customer service when the management is in. (Otherwise I've had REALLY great experience with the staff in the past!)<//review>

< Text>
A truly unique and epicly (epically?) awesome record store! They have a wide selection of all the stuff you want that's HARD TO FIND. I'm glad I live local to this one... perfect place for all your oldschool music needs!

Also, I'd like to add details of an actual experience. I was to see Depeche Mode in May 2018. I really wanted the Violator hoodie to go with me, but... they didn't have my size. BUT, They ordered it for me and it was ready for pickup just minutes before I arrived to check on that! Also got some Decals for the car. Overall, 100‚òÜs this place rocks!<//Text>

< review>
I love my car and it took me some time to find it.  Nori was helpful in this very long day.  I recommend bringing your own hand sanitizer, coffee, water, snacks etc.  You won't be offered anything.  I did however leave with a great car that I absolutely love.  MBZ Calabasas definitely has the greatest choice of cars and you are bound to find the  car with accessories you want here.   I came from sort of far away so I had done my homework. I would come here again and highly recommend.<//review>

<Text>This is the only car dealership I ever want to deal with again! By far the best car buying experience I've ever had.

From the start, working with Tracy from online sales was a great experience. She was knowledgeable and responsive. Most importantly, she was honest. It felt so good to be true that I was expecting the 'hustle' to come when I arrived.

When I got to the dealership, Tracy was great and introduced me to David, the sales manager. Would he be the one who changes things on me? Nope. He actually made the deal even better! That's right, he lowered the price AFTER we made the 150 mile drive to the dealership. Something I've never heard of before. That's it. I knew the catch would come when talking to finance.

When I got in with Raja, I texted my brother and told him the way part was done, but finance always had a trick up their sleeve. To my shock, Raja kept it real, gave us a great rate (1.9%) and didn't slide in any hidden fees. The amount financed was 43 cents lower than the "out the door" price that Tracy and David had promised, which was about $600 less than day we drove up for.

These don't seem like huge reductions and obviously I'm being facetious with the 43 cents, but this was never an experience I've had buying a car before. This is a dealership with class. Definitely worth the drive!</Text><pictures>None</pictures><Date>1602639624999< /Date>< resp>

I own several MBZ cars and I was taking them to another dealer in the valley for years, countless times I was disappointed with the quality of the service done, promises made and broken. So I decided to give Calabasas MBZ a try that is when I met with Kyle Wiens a service manager there, what can I say this guy is the best along with Angel the service director he goes above and beyond to make you the customer happy! I have never been treated this way from other dealerships with the utmost respect everything from start to finish was done in a very professional way.

When I brought my AMG GT C in for service there were some difficult challenges to deal with and each and everyone one of them was handled by Kyle & Angel. They got all of them done and truly took care of me. Also, the technician Juan is remarkable in the quality of workmanship and the passion he has for the cars he works on is very evident, like they say Juan is the first tech there in the morning and the last to leave at night he has tremendous pride in his workmanship. It shows!

All of this team has old school integrity & values you just don't find anymore! I feel blessed and lucky that I found these guys. I'm a Real Estate Broker in the Calabasas area I will be referring all my real estate associates that own Mercedes- Benz to this team without any hesitation! I would rate all of them with 10 stars if I could.

Thanks again for a great experience.

Ron Green<//Text>< pics>

The posting was so new there wasn't even a picture (it turns out the car was in detailing being made into almost new condition). I was there in a few hours (luckily because I wasn't the only one interested) and worked with Alfredo De Leon. It was a cash deal and I didn't get any upsell which was appreciated. I met with Jason McCann, the service manager who is the nicest guy and even though he knew I didn't live near Calabasas and so wouldn't be servicing the car there, explained so much about the car that he really gave me confidence in my purchase. I would definitely trust him with any service on the car if I lived anywhere near this dealership.
Something special that happened was that the detailing was going to take 2 days and my wife and I would pick up the car on Saturday, but a problem with a seam in the cab convertible top delayed pick up until Monday. My wife would be at work on Monday and I didn't want to spring for Uber/Lyft and complained to Alfredo who volunteered to pick me up and drove the 45 minutes each way. That's service, especially on a used car deal! My wife and I are so happy with the car. Thanks Mercedes Benz of Calabasas.< /Review>< Gmap_id>

<Review>After searching all over LA and Orange county for the best price on the new vehicle I wanted, MB of Calabasas had the best deal and I purchased the car from them.   That was 7 years ago and during that time and trying other dealers for service, I always came back to here. Many people don't realize that the dealerships charge different rates for the same A and B Services.  MB of Calabasas always won the price war and got me back in the door.  When my car was out of the factory warranty,  I bought the extended warranty, along with the pre-paid service for the next 3 years.  At that point I certainly could have gone to any dealer,  but I still made the trek from South Bay to Calabasas because of who they are and the great experience I had always received from them.   At this dealer, they didn't try to upsell me like two others did.   The service managers stayed pretty consistent, they always had an MB loaner ready for me, and every person I came in contact with made me feel important.  From the porter, cashier, loaner car agent, service manager, to the receptionist, they all are always nice, respectful, and have good attitudes. They are thorough with the car and conservative with service recommendations.  I've never had any issues with them, or the car.  This has been the best car I've ever owned and the best care I've ever had at a dealership!  Kudos to the GM of this dealer.  He or she is doing it right!

I'm going to miss them!  Sadly, my warranty and pre-paid maintenance is done and not renewable,  so I'll be finding a good independent service guy now in my neighborhood.   When I'm ready for my next MB, you can bet I'm coming back to MB of Calabasas.   They are the best in LA county hands down and I highly recommend them!< /Review><pics>None<//pics>< Response>

<user_name>Amanda Lauren Arnold< /user_name>< Date>
1464150627276<//Date>
<rating>5<//rating>< Text>
First off let me begin by saying the service was impeccable. It began with my Sales Representative Nick Argos. Nick greeted me and my friend immediately upon arriving to the dealership. Unfortunately, by the time I got there the vehicle I came to test drive and purchase was in the process of being sold. I was devastated and Nick could see it on my face.

He led us to his desk and explained I did not have to worry because Sonic Automotive Mercedes had multiple dealerships and I could select a vehicle from any of their dealerships to have it shipped down. This gave me hope because Mercedes Benz of Calabasas is one of the smaller Mercedes dealerships I have visited and I knew they did not have a similar model to the vehicle I came to purchase.

Within a matter of minutes Nick identified a newer, lower mileage vehicle that was only $5,000 more than the one I came for. It was practically new, 2015, 6,000 miles, C250 Coupe; I was in car love!! <3

Nick ordered the car to be delivered to Mercedes Benz of Calabasas immediately. He provided me with his mobile number and promised me he would keep me updated on the vehicles status. Nick stayed true to his word, he called and text me with each update he received. He even texted me pictures of the vehicle when it finally arrived, which was a few days later.

I came in the following weekend to purchase the vehicle and Nick had it ready for me in the showing room. The vehicle was squeaky clean, filled with gas, and had a note on the window reading "Congratulations on your new Mercedes Benz Amanda!" Everything was so perfect but then it came down to doing business.

Nick introduced me to Mehrad Navid their Financial Director. Mehrad was very kind, fast, and he listened. He asked me what I needed my payments to be and worked with me to get them where I was comfortable. At the end of it he provided me the lowest APR Mercedes could offer me, GAP, extended unlimited mileage warranty, and 2 years unlimited maintenance at an affordable monthly payment. I walked away with a newer vehicle with a unique Keyless Go feature (keyless entry and push to start) and better deal than my original Mercedes and the monthly payment were only slightly higher but definitely in my price range.

I drove away ecstatic! The only thing that could have been better was traffic. Exactly a week later Nick followed up with me to ensure I was still satisfied with my purchase. I am and I sincerely appreciate Mercedes Benz of Calabasas. I recommend visiting this dealership if you are seeking exceptional customer service and top quality Certified Preowned Mercedes Benzes.</Text>

< Text>
These people are scam artists. They take in previously leased cars, patch up visible damage, certify them, and sell them to the public.

We purchased a certified pre-owned vehicle, took it home, 2 days later we noticed three small holes in the windshield that appeared to be made by a tool. We immediately called the dealership and received no assistance.

We brought the car in, the manager Jose Leyva accused me of causing the damage myself (ie. rock hitting windshield, vandalism). They treated us like criminals, although, they reluctantly agreed to fix the glass but with the attitude that we should be grateful to them.

Now, when the windshield repair company saw the glass, they reported that the windshield, ‚Äúcould not be repaired because it has already been fix by someone else and the holes were made by a drill in the process of a previous repair.‚Äù After speaking with many credible people (other Mercedes dealership employees, the windshield repair technician, and an attorney) it seems that the dealership knew about the original damage, repaired the glass, stamped the car as ‚Äúcertified‚Äù and sold it to us.   NOTE: When a vehicle is certified pre-owned, the glass is supposed to be the original glass without damage.

After the report by the windshield repair company they sent a new windshield which was fine, however, had it not been for the this one HONEST man (windshield repair technician), we would have been stuck with a broken windshield on a newly purchased vehicle.

The entire process took months. It was frustrating and a complete battle. I was forced to hire an attorney to support me through this unjust situation. I will never again associate with this dealership and hope that this review helps people to be cautious<//Text>

<user_name>Kerri Randles</user_name><text>Okay, I don't think I've ever had a better experience buying a car. If you are thinking of buying or leasing a Mercedes Benz, I don't care how far away you live from Calabasas, California... it's worth the trip!! Mark Matias and Andrew Wallop guided me through the most pleasant experience, dealing with my trade-in, a recently challenged credit score, and the reality of buying a car in a depressed market. Honestly, they could have sold me a KIA and I would have bought it. The lesson here is: NEVER SETTLE.

After test-driving the E-Class and C-Class, they did their best to get me into the E-Class, a step up, when the C-Class ended up being just fine for me. There was never the typical detached vibe of a car salesman. These men were more than car salesmen. They were men who have lived lives and have momentarily graced Mercedes Benz with their presence. No doubt, more cars have sold at this location since they arrived. After several hours, and lunch on them, never any nervousness that the transaction wouldn't go through... They made me the proud driver of my first Mercedes on that balmy, hot day in the Valley. It actually drizzled on my way home, and they offered to re-detail the car for me a few days later...

I actually had separation anxiety driving away from the place, and look forward to going back for the detail, just to say 'hello'!!! The real reason I'm writing this though is that we live in a world of instant gratification and immediacy. Celebrity and status. It gets rarer that someone on the street looks you in the eyes. The common thread that connects us all has been broken. We are all disconnected. Especially in the pursuit of money, things, and ironically happiness. It's the little things though, like these kind of interactions, that give us hope in humanity again.

Signed, a VERY satisfied patron, driver, and human being.

Kerri Randles< /text><user>102367038396518237988< /user><rate>5<//rate>< time>

Sounded good/fair, except actually getting the $300 has now become more irritating than the water pump going bad in the first place. Despite personally taking an original copy of the repair receipt to the used car manager as instructed more than three weeks ago, there now is no record of the receipt and no check for $300.  During my THIRD trip to this place today, they once again said they needed a receipt to start the process over again. You might ask why I went there personally three times instead of calling. You try calling this place and you will soon know. I now believe they never intended to reimburse for the repair. They just assumed I would forget about it since it's only $300 at a Mercedes dealership. Which is probably what I would have done if I hadn't become convinced it was all just a scam. I've spent more time standing in the lobby of this dealership waiting on someone to actually give me an answer than it took for my mechanic to put in a new water pump... at half the price quoted at Mercedes Benz of Calabasas. I shopped for a new car at this dealership a little more than a year ago and walked away because it was just too chaotic and disorganized. My bad for having a short memory. If you are in the market for a Mercedes, it's well worth the drive to Santa Monica.<//Review><Rate>1<//Rate><Pics>None<//Pics></record>

We were referred to another staff member who had no idea either and started to chase us through all three levels of the entire parking lot in order to look for the car which, in the end, was still not to be found. That guy checked with another colleague who made a phone call and found out that the car is actually in the shop, which was already locked and nobody knew where the key was. As an update:

After this review was written, I was contacted by the Service Director Angel and the Service Lane Manager Jason. They both heard me out and vowed to figure out a way to fix the situation. They were prompt and got back to me the same day and were able to pull some strings in order to find a way to cover all of the costs of the repair.

I appreciate the collaboration the two of them did and fought for the correction of this problem.

Thank you for both of your help! You guys are awesome.

Original Post -

Avoid at all cost!!
I had a recent "Lane assist inoperative" warning on my dash and brought the car to get it checked out. To recap - the car was bought from Mercedes Benz of Calabasas as Certified Pre-own and is still under warranty. Called and made an appointment and the receptionist advised there may be a charge for diagnostic charges just in case if the car was in accident that warranty would not cover the charges. My car has never been in any accident so I took the car in. After the diagnostic test, they noted that heating element in the windshield was defective and the ENTIRE windshield needs to be replace and to top it off, that CPO warranty does not cover the windshield. They said that I need to pay the $180 diagnostic fee and on top of that it's $2,200 to replace the entire windshield as the heating element is not a part that can be replaced.

I was infuriated. I spoke to the service representative (Ryan Collins) who said that their salesman don't explain the CPO coverages well and this isn't the first time this issue has happened. Is that a joke? For customers that pay a premium to buy a car from this place to have the peace of mind of having coverage you don't think that you should explain this situation to them? Really?

I got my car back and called corporate. Corporate said that after their investigation they will cover the parts to fix this ordeal but labor is under the discretion of the dealership. Ryan called me back and quoted by a 5.5 hr job and a quote of $1,000 + for the install. Forget Non-Mercedes glass companies that charge $400 to $500 for the entire job, I have the parts covered and they still want to charge me $1000 plus to install. As spectacle as I was, I wanted to give the benefit of the doubt to them but I called Mercedes Benz of Encino and their service dept. said the labor would actually be 2.5 to 3.0 hrs and quoted me $450 for the installation. As a customer of the Calabasas dealership and a patron of getting my car service at this location, I feel that my trust has been taken advantage of throughout this entire car process from purchase to now repair.

I was told that it is best to get a hold of the service manager through email but again have yet to hear back. Like I said before, stay away from this place.< /text>

< user_name>
Mike Ricardo< /user_name>
< time>
1511201572387< /time>
<rate>1< /rate>< Review>
These guys are FRAUDS!
Go ahead and Google: Auto loan payment packing. This is what THEY do!

Walked in the other night hoping to close a deal. I had spoken to their sales manager, Sunil, previously and we agreed to financing terms which WERE NOT HONORED. The sales manager, Sunil, had run my credit, presented me the terms and the following day when I come back to close the deal, the guy in finance, Sang, is telling me terms that DO NOT match what their sales manager Sunil presented me AFTER they had already ran my credit the previous night.

It seems they had some miscommunication as the interest rate their sales manager presented me was HIGHER than the one I saw in finance despite my credit ALREADY being ran. Once I was in finance, Sang gives me the LOWER interest rate, gives no mention of the original HIGHER rate Sunil had presented me and continues to tell me my payments will be still be HIGHER despite the new LOWER interest rate and the rest of the deal's terms being IDENTICAL.

It's clear that these guys attempted to close me on a HIGHER interest rate regardless of what the BANK had offered. It's called payment packing, it is illegal and I'm sure it has happened to countless customers. They're able to do this by having you focus on only certain aspects of the deal. With your mind on whatever that aspect is, they move around your down payment, give you "discounts" on backend products (warranty, gap etc) and in this case, FRAUDULENTLY inflate your interest rate in the name of their own profit.

Do yourself a favor and STAY AWAY from Mercedes Benz of Calabasas. Don't let the franchise fool you, these guys are your run of the mill snake oil salesmen and you'll have less of a headache and maybe even more honesty on a used car lot.</Review>
